The code statements that lead to the bug are:
```java
// No restriction on file writing
```
Reason:
The file producer did not have any restrictions in place, allowing files to be written outside of the designated starting directory. This lack of validation posed a security risk by enabling unauthorized access to parent or root directories.

The code statements that fix the bug are:
```java
protected boolean jailStartingDirectory = true;
public void setJailStartingDirectory(boolean jailStartingDirectory) {
    this.jailStartingDirectory = jailStartingDirectory;
}
```
Reason:
The introduction of the `jailStartingDirectory` parameter, set to `true` by default, restricts file writing to the starting directory and its subdirectories. This change enhances security by preventing the application from writing files to unauthorized locations outside the designated directory.

